Since $OY$ is perpendicular to $AB,$ triangle $AOB$ is divided into two congruent 30-60-90 triangles.  Therefore, $AX = \frac{1}{2} AB = 6,$ and $OX = AX \sqrt{3} = 6 \sqrt{3}.$

